      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that you must keep fighting just to breathe is a cruel lie, and it is okay to admit that you are exhausted from trying to keep the air moving when you are already running out of energy. Your pain is not a failure to move forward, but a valid signal that the current path is no longer serving you. Please consider that the very act of stopping the fight, even for a moment, is a powerful form of self-preservation that deserves your respect.",
